<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Hotspot on Saitech</title><link>https://saitech.blog/tags/hotspot/</link><description>Recent content in Hotspot on Saitech</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 15 May 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://saitech.blog/tags/hotspot/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Exploring Alternative Firmwares for Routers</title><link>https://saitech.blog/p/exploring-alternative-firmwares-for-routers/</link><pubDate>Thu, 15 May 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saitech.blog/p/exploring-alternative-firmwares-for-routers/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/exploring-alternative-firmwares-for-routers/1.png" alt="Featured image of post Exploring Alternative Firmwares for Routers" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;My router didn‚Äôt support &lt;strong&gt;Client Bridge&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;Repeater Bridge&lt;/strong&gt; mode out of the box.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sometimes when my internet goes down, I share a mobile hotspot from my phone. But to &lt;strong&gt;distribute that connection over LAN and Wi-Fi&lt;/strong&gt;, I needed a router that supports client mode + AP. Unfortunately, my &lt;strong&gt;TP-Link Archer C6&lt;/strong&gt; couldn‚Äôt do this‚Ä¶ until I replaced the official firmware with &lt;strong&gt;OpenWRT&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="-check-compatibility"&gt;‚úÖ Check Compatibility
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Make sure your device is supported:
üîó &lt;a class="link" href="https://openwrt.org/toh/start" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;https://openwrt.org/toh/start&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Download the &lt;strong&gt;exact&lt;/strong&gt; firmware version for your hardware revision.
‚ö†Ô∏è &lt;em&gt;Double-check your model and version before flashing!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then upgrade the firmware as you normally would via the router‚Äôs web UI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="-setting-up-openwrt-using-luci-web-interface-"&gt;‚öôÔ∏è Setting Up OpenWRT (Using LUCI Web Interface )
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Access your router: &lt;a class="link" href="http://192.168.1.1" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;http://192.168.1.1&lt;/a&gt;
Set your password if prompted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="connect-to-your-hotspot--client-mode-"&gt;Connect to Your Hotspot ( Client Mode )
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go to &lt;strong&gt;Network ‚Üí Wireless&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click &lt;strong&gt;Scan&lt;/strong&gt; next to the wireless radio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Find your mobile hotspot, click &lt;strong&gt;Join Network&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enter your hotspot password ( Wireless Security )&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mode:&lt;/strong&gt; Client&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Network:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;wwan&lt;/code&gt; (create if needed)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Save &amp;amp; Apply&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
